Subject: [PATCH] patch 0899: Turnaround filter loosened +
 DecisionTierBlock-style empty state
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User: "i mean tier one or tier 2 format" - the empty state was a
custom amber card with a different chrome than Tier 1 / Tier 2 in
the populated state, so it visually appeared as a separate UX
language on the page.

Two changes:

1. Filter loosened: take top 5 by totalScore from mb_turnaround_scored_v1.
   Previous filter required isBestCandidate OR
   (archetype=TURNAROUND AND totalScore>=60), which excluded every
   row on uploads where the engine had not flagged any BEST
   candidate. Now any non-null row with a symbol qualifies; sort by
   totalScore picks the actual best 5.

2. Empty-state rebuilt to match DecisionTierBlock exactly:
     - Same cardStyle base
     - borderColor: #F59E0B70 (amber, matches when populated)
     - background: gradient(180deg, #F59E0B14 -> transparent)
     - Header: "🎯 TIER 1 — TURNAROUND BUY-ZONE (0)" same font weight
       + letter-spacing as Tier 1
     - "ACTION NOW" pill chip with same styling as Tier 1
     - Description block under header, same gray 11px text
     - Empty-state message in the candidate-grid slot, same amber
       border / 10% background tint as a populated candidate card
   When the user uploads turnaround data, the same outer shell is
   reused (just delegated to DecisionTierBlock); the visual
   transition between empty and populated is now seamless.
---
 frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/page.tsx | 66 +++++++++++++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 46 insertions(+), 20 deletions(-)

diff --git a/frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/page.tsx b/frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/page.tsx
index 914a46b..bf802cc 100644
--- a/frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/page.tsx
+++ b/frontend/src/app/(dashboard)/page.tsx
@@ -384,8 +384,14 @@ function buildSyncState(): Pick<HomeState, 'tier1' | 'tier2' | 'tier3' | 'turnar
   const turnaroundRaw: any[] = (() => {
     try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('mb_turnaround_scored_v1') || '[]') || []; } catch { return []; }
   })();
+  // PATCH 0899 — Loosened filter. Previous gate required isBestCandidate=true
+  // OR (archetype=TURNAROUND AND totalScore>=60), which excluded every row
+  // on uploads where the scoring engine hadn't tagged any row as BEST. Now
+  // just take the top-5 by totalScore — the user's actual best candidates
+  // surface even when archetype/best flags aren't set. Only filter out
+  // null/garbage rows.
   const turnaroundTier1: TierAction[] = (turnaroundRaw || [])
-    .filter((r: any) => r && (r.isBestCandidate === true || (r.archetype === 'TURNAROUND' && (r.totalScore ?? 0) >= 60)))
+    .filter((r: any) => r && typeof r.symbol === 'string' && r.symbol.length > 0)
     .sort((a: any, b: any) => (b.totalScore ?? 0) - (a.totalScore ?? 0))
     .slice(0, 5)
     .map((r: any) => {
@@ -2019,37 +2025,57 @@ export default function HomeDashboard() {
